---
title: Toasty Pesto Gnocchi with Green Beans, Sun-Dried Tomatoes, and Parmesan
description: Whether you call them *nyo-kee*, *nyock-ee*, or something else entirely, these potato dumplings are delicious, for sure. How could they not be with a good dollop of pesto to coat them in cheesy, herbaceous flavor? But just to make sure that you’re not left wanting for more Italian-style flair, we’re throwing in sun-dried tomatoes, snappy green beans, and a sprinkling of Parmesan cheese.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5afb41c330006c50a3613de2-58152b86.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/toasty-pesto-gnocchi-5afb41c330006c50a3613de2-6bf264d8.pdf
cuisine: Fusion
author: HelloFresh
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 560 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 63 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 23 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 1450 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/toasty-pesto-gnocchi-5afb41c330006c50a3613de2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot{} of @salted water{} to a boil. Trim, then thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%oz}. Cut @green beans{6%oz} into 2-inch pieces. Roughly chop @sun-dried tomatoes{1.5%oz}. Cut @lemon{1} into wedges.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms to pan and cook, tossing, until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Once water is boiling, add green beans to pot. Cook until just barely tender, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from pot with a #slotted spoon{}, place in a #strainer{}, and rinse under very cold water (keep the pot of boiling water on stove for the gnocchi). Remove green beans from strainer and set aside.

Add @gnocchi{9%oz} to same pot of boiling water. Cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, ~{1-2%minutes}, then drain, tossing gently in strainer to remove excess moisture.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in pan used for mushrooms over medium-high heat. Add gnocchi to pan and cook, tossing, until lightly browned, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Add @pesto{2%oz}, sun-dried tomatoes, green beans, half the @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, and mushrooms to pan with gnocchi. Cook, tossing, until combined and warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Divide between #bowls{}, then sprinkle with remaining Parmesan. Serve with lemon wedges for squeezing over.